features: Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong toilet paper is soft, strong & made sustainably for a comfy, reliable clean.
Each Mega Roll has 295 2-ply sheets that are 5X stronger & more durable than the leading value brand of toilet paper when wet.
We’ve planted over 5 million trees through our partnership with the Arbor Day Foundation.

body.description: Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong® Toilet Paper offers comfort, strength, and sustainability all in one toilet tissue pack. Each premium 2-ply sheet is 5X stronger and more durable than the leading value brand of toilet paper when wet -- all created using responsible manufacturing and sourcing practices. Our proprietary manufacturing technology is energy-efficient while providing the soft and strong toilet paper you expect. The trees used to create Quilted Northern® toilet paper products come from well-managed FSC® certified forests and other responsible sources. And to top it off, two trees are planted for each tree used through our partnership with the Arbor Day Foundation. Each Mega Roll has 295 sheets, so in total you are getting over 5,300 sheets of Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong toilet paper! This bulk toilet paper pack contains 18 Mega Rolls of Quilted Northern Ultra Soft and Strong® bath tissue in a paper package that you can recycle right at home in your curbside bin. Look no further for an unbeatable combination of softness, strength and sustainability - choose Quilted Northern Ultra Soft & Strong® toilet paper.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No Stupid Red bears wavingtheir tail ends!
reviews.reviewText: Costco TP is loaded with dust, but works ok. Charmin is too soft and often is scented and simply smells like a bathroom odor cover. Northern doesn't have a scent. Northern holds together well and does a great job. Northern is plenty soft enough that my boss... I mean my spouse, likes it more than any other brand and she doesn't care what it cost. I do and this is reasonably priced as well. So there you have it. No stupid red bears enjoying the go.... don't bears go in the woods anyway?!?

reviews.reviewText: Someone one said to me: there are so many places you can reign in your budget, toilet paper is a simple pleasure and should not be one of them. That stuck with me, so now I get the good stuff, and this is the good stuff. Soft, sturdy, lasts because a little goes a long way, and doesn’t clog the toilet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Soft where it needs to be!
reviews.reviewText: I started purchasing this product during the TP shortages because it is a brand I remembered from my youth. I used to use store brands, but as the shelves emptied, I turned to online sources. Amazon has delivered. This TP is soft, absorbent, and well packaged. I really like that it is wrapped in paper and not plastic. I know plastic can help prevent unintended moisture damage, but the paper does a good job containing and protecting the rolls. The large rolls last quite awhile for the three of us and we now have a stockpile for any future shortages that may occur. It is also nice this company works with their supplier and the Arbor Day Foundation to plant trees. I can feel better using this product and knowing my money isn't just flushed away, but helps to conserve a valuable resource, as well.
